An iframe is an HTML element used to embed another webpage inside the current webpage.

🔹 Simple definition
An iframe lets you load a completely separate HTML document within a section of your page.

🔹 Syntax
<iframe src="https://example.com"></iframe>

🔹 Real-time example
Think of:
You’re on a website
Inside it, you see a YouTube video, Google Map, or payment page

Those are usually loaded using an iframe.
🔹 Why iframe is used
Embed videos (YouTube)
Show maps (Google Maps)
Load ads or external content
Integrate third-party pages (payment gateways, chat widgets)
👉 Selenium cannot directly interact with elements inside iframe
👉 You must switch to iframe first

🔹 Types of switching in Selenium
driver.switchTo().frame(index);          // by index
driver.switchTo().frame("nameOrId");     // by name/id
driver.switchTo().frame(WebElement);     // by WebElement
driver.switchTo().defaultContent(); or  driver.switchTo().parentFrame(); // come back to main page

If you don’t switch to iframe:
👉 You will get NoSuchElementException